What you need to know:  The 21-year-old Lekuya blew away the field, leading from gun-to-tape to triumph in 32 minutes and 42.8 seconds during the second edition of the championships at the Ngong Racecourse on SaturdayThe first of the five laps race turned out to be a three-horse race with Lekuya, David Lewano from Western and Rift Valley's Kelvin Kiplagat breaking away from the restLekuya would easily assert his presence to build his lead before edging out Lewano to second place in 32:59.9 as Kiplagat locked 33:38.7 for third place